    <p>Few works in this genre are as emo­tional and un­set­tling as Pris­on­ers (2013), which asks how far you would go if your child were to dis­ap­pear.</p>
    <p>Nightcrawl­er (2014) is a sav­age, funny por­trait of a na­tion ad­dicted to the 24-hour cy­cle of crime cov­er­age.</p>
    <p>With Seven (1995), di­rec­tor David Fincher showed that style, as much as plot, mat­ters in a crime story.</p>
    <p>Layer Cake (2004), which throws a sweary, satir­i­cal spot­light on the co­caine smug­gling busi­ness in Eng­land, is filled with ac­tors on their way up: Daniel Craig, Ben Whishaw, Sally Hawkins, Si­enna Miller and a baby-faced Tom</p>
    <p>Hardy.</p>
    <p>Watch on Net­flix: Seven (1995)</p>
    <p>Layer Cake (2004) Pris­on­ers (2013) Nightcrawl­er (2014)</p>

